PROJECT TITLE

Personal Expense Tracker System

1. Problem Statement

Many individuals struggle to monitor their daily expenses and savings effectively. Traditional methods such as maintaining notebooks or spreadsheets are time-consuming and prone to errors. There is a need for a digital solution that helps users record, categorize, and analyze their expenses efficiently, enabling better financial planning and budget management.

2. Project Objectives

- To develop a user-friendly expense tracking application.
- To record and manage daily income and expenses.
- To categorize expenses for better financial analysis.
- To monitor monthly spending and savings patterns.
- To generate reports and visual summaries of expenses.
- To help users make informed financial decisions.

3. Module List

1. User Registration and Login Module
2. Income Management Module
3. Expense Management Module
4. Expense Category Management Module
5. Budget Planning Module
6. Reports and Analytics Module
7. Notification and Reminder Module
8. User Profile Management Module
9. Dashboard Module

4. Technologies Used

Frontend

HTML, CSS, JavaScript, Bootstrap

Backend

Python (Flask/Django)

Database

MySQL

Additional Tools

GitHub, VS Code, Chart.js

5. Expected Outcome

The system will enable users to track their financial activities effectively by recording income and expenses in a centralized platform. Users can monitor their spending habits, manage budgets, and generate reports for better financial planning. The application will improve financial awareness and support smarter money management.

6. Future Enhancements

- AI-based expense prediction and analysis.
- Integration with banking applications.
- Mobile application support.
- Voice-based expense entry.
- Personalized financial recommendations.
